          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Cross-sections for the elastic recoil of hydrogen",
                " isotopes for high energy helium ions"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "VDGT"
                ],
                "institute": "1USASC"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Sandia's 6 MV EN Tandem accelerator"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The incident helium beams current on target during the",
                " cross-section measurements was about 3 nano-Amperes.",
                " The projected beam profile on target, tilted at",
                " 75 degree relative to the sample normal, is 1 mm x",
                " 1.4 mm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                " Energy loss in the target calculated with the",
                " SRIM-2000 code."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A particle telescope is used to separate and",
                " detect hydrogen isotopes. The particle telescope is",
                " composed of a 109 microm thick Mylar range foil",
                " followed by a curved aperture."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A thin silicon surface barrier detector,",
                " Ortec TD-040-300-75-S, of thickness 65.2 microm and",
                " active area 300mm2 is located behind the curved",
                " aperture."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A thick silicon surface barrier detector,",
                " Ortec BU-018-300-300, follows the thin DE detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The target films used in this experiment were produced",
                " by e-beam deposition of 500 nm of erbium onto",
                " molybdenum substrates. Hydriding of the erbium was",
                " accomplished by exposure of the erbium layer to an",
                " overpressure of the appropriate gas at a prescribed",
                " temperature and pressure yielding target film",
                " stoichiometry of about 2:1 (i.e. ErH2, ErD2 and ErT2)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Beam energy calibration was carried out using the",
                " 19F(p,g) resonance at the proton energy of 0.827 MeV",
                " as well as the two resonance reactions H(19F,g) and",
                " H(19F,g) at the fluorine energy of 16.440 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
